{"id": "0d3e86d044bd4121a8782df201a21ff7", "timestamp": "2025-12-10 21:59:23", "name": "Scientist0", "content": "Thought: The proposed research direction addresses a fundamental challenge in single-view 3D reconstruction—pose-shape entanglement—by leveraging intrinsic geometric symmetries as self-supervised priors for learning invariant representations. Unlike conventional approaches that rely on large multi-view datasets or assume pose-aligned training data, this method actively mitigates data bias through symmetry-aware canonicalization, group-equivariant latent regularization, and contrastive learning. It introduces architectural and theoretical innovations that are both empirically testable and scalable across object categories without requiring manual symmetry annotations. The integration of geometric priors into deep learning not only improves robustness to orientation variations but also enhances interpretability and generalization—key requirements for real-world deployment in robotics and AR/VR. Furthermore, the proposed Latent Invariance Score provides a direct metric for evaluating the core objective: pose invariance in latent space. This topic is innovative, technically feasible, and fills a critical gap in current methods by shifting from post-hoc disentanglement to proactive prevention of pose leakage via structured learning. Its potential impact on improving generalization under arbitrary viewpoints makes it a timely and significant contribution to the field.\n\nTopic: ```json{\"Selected Topic\": \"Self-Supervised Symmetry-Aware Disentanglement for Pose-Invariant Latent Representations in Single-View 3D Reconstruction\"}```", "role": "assistant", "url": null, "metadata": null, "_colored_name": "\u001b[95mScientist0\u001b[0m"}
{"id": "956579f0a8ed44b38ee6dd2d33dccc1e", "timestamp": "2025-12-10 21:59:27", "name": "Scientist0", "content": "The selected research topic focuses on developing self-supervised, symmetry-aware disentanglement to achieve pose-invariant latent representations in single-view 3D reconstruction. It addresses the core issue of pose-shape entanglement by leveraging intrinsic geometric symmetries as priors for canonicalization, using group-equivariant regularization and a learnable symmetry predictor—without requiring annotated data. The approach integrates with existing architectures, introduces the Latent Invariance Score for evaluation, and enables proactive prevention of pose leakage through structured learning. This method is innovative, empirically verifiable, and scalable, with strong potential for improving generalization and robustness in real-world applications like robotics and AR/VR.", "role": "assistant", "url": null, "metadata": null, "_colored_name": "\u001b[95mScientist0\u001b[0m"}
